# tests/e2e/

End-to-end tests that drive the system the way a real user or peer would —
through its presentation layer, against the real stack, with all
adapters wired up.

Belongs here:
- HTTP scenarios that hit a running server and assert on responses
- CLI scenarios that invoke the binary and assert on stdout/exit codes
- Cross-feature flows that span multiple use cases

Does **not** belong here:
- Anything that mocks part of the stack — go a layer in to `../integration/`
- Anything that doesn't need the full system — go a layer in to `../unit/`

These tests are slow and brittle by nature. Keep them focused on critical
user flows; let unit and integration tests carry the coverage load.

Canonical reference: `{{ ai_folder }}/instructions/general/testing.md`.
